18. Solutions in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Solutions are used to transport apps and components from one environment to another environment â€” like from development to testing or production 
ğŸ‘‰ Solution can contains one or more apps, as well as other components like Dataverse tables, flows & other lot more.
ğŸ‘‰ This enables structured deployments through solution export/import, improves version control, and supports effective Application Lifecycle Management (ALM).

ğŸ”¹ There are two main types of Solutions:
1. Unmanaged Solution: During Development, I used an unmanaged solution for easy editing and team collabortion.
2. Managed Solution:  Once the app was finalized, I exported the app as a managed solution and deployed to the production environment.  
                      â€” Managed Solution are read-only; can't be edited directly.

âœ… Environment Variables are reusable configuration settings used within a solution. 
   â€” they store values like SharePoint site URLs or API keys, that may change between environments such as development, testing, or production.

Example:
ğŸ‘‰ In one project, I built an onboarding app inside a Solution, and then exported it from Dev and imported it into the QA and Production environments smoothly.
