21. What is Pagination in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Pagination in Power Apps refers to the technique of loading and displaying large data sets into smaller, manageable chunks (pages) 
   â€” instead of retrieving all records at once.

ğŸ”¹ Why pagination is needed:
ğŸ‘‰ To improve performance by avoiding loading all records at once.
ğŸ‘‰ To handle delegation limits (e.g., SharePoint, Dataverse often return max 500 or 2000 records).
ğŸ‘‰ To create user-friendly UI where users can navigate records in steps (Next/Previous).

âœ… Where is Pagination Used?
ğŸ‘‰ Canvas Apps, especially in Gallery controls showing SharePoint, Dataverse, or SQL data 1000+ records.
ğŸ‘‰ You want to show 10 records per page using a gallery.



